					["gt0001"] = (TERM) <
						text = <"International Prostate Symptom Score (IPSS) Assessment">
						description = <"The International Prostate Symptom Score (IPSS) is used to assist in the rapid diagnosis of Benign Prostatic Hyperplasia (BPH), as well as monitor the symptoms of the disease over time. The questionnaire consists first of 7 questions addressing how the patient has experienced the following symptoms over the past month: incomplete emptying (of the bladder), frequency, intermittency, urgency, weak stream, straining, and nocturia. The responses are scored from 0 (no symptoms) to 5 (worst possible) and a score of ≤7 indicates mild symptoms, 8-19 moderate symptoms, and 20-35 severe symptoms.
 An 8th question which addresses the perceived quality of life as a result of the urinary symptoms, does not contribute to the overall score or its assessment.
">
